org.sbrubbles.conditio.policies

Interface ReturnTypePolicy<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type to be returned by signal.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Policies
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ReturnTypePolicy<T>
    The type a signal invocation expects to return.

      • getExpectedType

        Class<T> getExpectedType()
        The type signal expects to return. May be null if signal doesn't expect to return a value.
        Returns:
        the type signal expects to return. May be null if signal doesn't expect to return a value.

      • cast

        default T cast(Object value)
        Casts an object to the class or interface in this policy. Returns null if this policy doesn't define an expected type.
        Parameters:
        value - the object to be cast.
        Returns:
        the given value after casting, or null if this policy doesn't define an expected type.
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - if the given value is not null and is not assignable to T.

      • expects

        static <R> ReturnTypePolicy<R> expects(Class<R> type)
        A policy to expect values compatible with the given type.
        Parameters:
        type - the expected return type.
        Returns:
        a policy to expect values compatible with the given type.

      • ignore

        static <R> ReturnTypePolicy<R> ignore()
        A policy to ignore any returned values. Therefore, there is no expected return type.
        Returns:
        a policy to ignore any returned values.
